ed5000SysBootDate.name: ed5000SysBootDate
ed5000SysBootDate.description: The date and time of the last IPL

ed5000SysFirmwareVersion.name: ed5000SysFirmwareVersion
ed5000SysFirmwareVersion.description: The current version of the firmware.

ed5000SysTypeNum.name: ed5000SysTypeNum
ed5000SysTypeNum.description: This object identifies ASCII type number for the unit.

ed5000SysModelNum.name: ed5000SysModelNum
ed5000SysModelNum.description: This object identifies ASCII model number for the unit.

ed5000SysMfg.name: ed5000SysMfg
ed5000SysMfg.description: This object identifies ASCII manufacturer for the unit.

ed5000SysPlantOfMfg.name: ed5000SysPlantOfMfg
ed5000SysPlantOfMfg.description: This object identifies ASCII plant of manufacturer for the unit.

ed5000SysSeqNum.name: ed5000SysSeqNum
ed5000SysSeqNum.description: This object identifies ASCII sequence number for the unit.

ed5000SysEcLevel.name: ed5000SysEcLevel
ed5000SysEcLevel.description: This object identifies ASCII EC level ID for the unit.

ed5000SysOemSerialNum.name: ed5000SysOemSerialNum
ed5000SysOemSerialNum.description: This object identifies ASCII OEM serial number for the unit

ed5000SysOperStatus.name: ed5000SysOperStatus
ed5000SysOperStatus.description: The current operational status of the switch. The values are defined as follow: operational (1), redundant-failure (2), minor-failure (3), major-failure (4), not-operational (5).

ed5000SysState.name: ed5000SysState
ed5000SysState.description: If the edOperStatus of the switch is operational, the switch will be in one of the four states: online(1), coming-online(2), offline(3), and going-offline(4).

ed5000SysAdmStatus.name: ed5000SysAdmStatus
ed5000SysAdmStatus.description: The desired administrative status of the switch. A management station may place the switch in a desired state by setting this object accordingly. The desired administrative status are online(1) and offline(2). The online means setting the switch to be accessible by an external Fibre Channel port, and offline means setting the switch to be inaccessible.

ed5000FruTable.name: ed5000FruTable
ed5000FruTable.description: A table that contains one entry for each module.

ed5000FruEntry.name: ed5000FruEntry
ed5000FruEntry.description: An entry containing the service parameters of the module.

ed5000FruCode.name: ed5000FruCode
ed5000FruCode.description: Field Replaceable Unit. A hardware component of the product that is replaceable as an entire unit. Each module defined in this MIB has a fixed FRU code. The values are defined as follow: fru-none (0) , fru-bkplane (1), fru-ctp (2), fru-mpc (3), fru-cmm (4), fru-fan (5), fru-power (6), fru-panel (7), fru-gsm (8), fru-gls (9), fru-glx (10), fru-lsm (11), fru-gxx (12).

ed5000FruPosition.name: ed5000FruPosition
ed5000FruPosition.description: This object identifies the position of the module. Port cards start from 1 to 8. All other cards start from 1 to 1 or 2.

ed5000FruStatus.name: ed5000FruStatus
ed5000FruStatus.description: This object identifies the operational status of the module. The active(1) state indicates that the current module is active. The backup(2) state indicates that the back up module is used. update-busy (3) state indicates that the module is in the updating process. The failed(4) state indicates that the current module is failed.

ed5000FruPartNumber.name: ed5000FruPartNumber
ed5000FruPartNumber.description: This object identifies the part number of the module.

ed5000FruSerialNumber.name: ed5000FruSerialNumber
ed5000FruSerialNumber.description: This object identifies the serial number of the module.

ed5000FruPowerOnHours.name: ed5000FruPowerOnHours
ed5000FruPowerOnHours.description: This object indicates the number of the hours that the FRU has been in operation.

ed5000FruTestDate.name: ed5000FruTestDate
ed5000FruTestDate.description: This object indicates final test date of the module.

ed5000PortTable.name: ed5000PortTable
ed5000PortTable.description: A table that contains one entry for each switch port (stitch only).

ed5000PortEntry.name: ed5000PortEntry
ed5000PortEntry.description: An entry containing the information of the switch port.

ed5000PortIndex.name: ed5000PortIndex
ed5000PortIndex.description: This object identifies the switch port.

ed5000PortPhyState.name: ed5000PortPhyState
ed5000PortPhyState.description: This object identifies the physical state of the port.

ed5000PortOpStatus.name: ed5000PortOpStatus
ed5000PortOpStatus.description: This object identifies the operational status of the port. The online state indicates that user frames can be passed.

ed5000PortAdmStatus.name: ed5000PortAdmStatus
ed5000PortAdmStatus.description: The desired state of the port. A management station may place the port in a desired state by setting this object accordingly. The testing(3) state indicates that no user frames can be passed. As the result of either explicit management action or per configuration information accessible by the switch, ed5000PortAdmStatus is then changed to either the online(1) or testing(3) states, or remains in the offline state.

ed5000PortTxWords.name: ed5000PortTxWords
ed5000PortTxWords.description: This object counts the number of Fibre Channel words that the port has transmitted.

ed5000PortRxWords.name: ed5000PortRxWords
ed5000PortRxWords.description: This object counts the number of Fibre Channel words that the port has received.

ed5000PortTxFrames.name: ed5000PortTxFrames
ed5000PortTxFrames.description: This object counts the number of (Fibre Channel) frames that the port has transmitted.

ed5000PortRxFrames.name: ed5000PortRxFrames
ed5000PortRxFrames.description: This object counts the number of (Fibre Channel) frames that the port has received.

ed5000PortRxC2Frames.name: ed5000PortRxC2Frames
ed5000PortRxC2Frames.description: This object counts the number of Class 2 frames that the port has received.

ed5000PortRxC3Frames.name: ed5000PortRxC3Frames
ed5000PortRxC3Frames.description: This object counts the number of Class 3 frames that the port has received.

ed5000PortRxLCs.name: ed5000PortRxLCs
ed5000PortRxLCs.description: This object counts the number of Link Control frames that the port has received.

ed5000PortRxMcasts.name: ed5000PortRxMcasts
ed5000PortRxMcasts.description: This object counts the number of Multicast frames that the port has received.

ed5000PortTooManyRdys.name: ed5000PortTooManyRdys
ed5000PortTooManyRdys.description: This object counts the number of 2.26 micro second intervals where the transmission of RDYs has priority over the transmission of frame traffic. (In 2.x releases and below, this counter gets incremented continuously and therefore has no meaning. In release 3.0 and above, it is always 0.)

ed5000PortNoTxCredits.name: ed5000PortNoTxCredits
ed5000PortNoTxCredits.description: This object counts the amount of time that frame transmission is blocked by a transmit credit of zero. This is sampled once every 120 53.125 MHZ clocks, and the counter is incremented by 1 if the condition is true.

ed5000PortRxEncFrs.name: ed5000PortRxEncFrs
ed5000PortRxEncFrs.description: This object counts the number of encoding error or disparity error inside or outside frames received.

ed5000PortRxCrcs.name: ed5000PortRxCrcs
ed5000PortRxCrcs.description: This object counts the number of CRC errors detected for frames received.

ed5000PortRxTruncs.name: ed5000PortRxTruncs
ed5000PortRxTruncs.description: This object counts the number of truncated frames that the port has received.

ed5000PortRxTooLongs.name: ed5000PortRxTooLongs
ed5000PortRxTooLongs.description: This object counts the number of received frames that are too long.

ed5000PortRxBadEofs.name: ed5000PortRxBadEofs
ed5000PortRxBadEofs.description: This object counts the number of received frames that have bad EOF delimiter.

ed5000PortRxBadOs.name: ed5000PortRxBadOs
ed5000PortRxBadOs.description: This object counts the number of invalid Ordered Sets received.

ed5000PortC3Discards.name: ed5000PortC3Discards
ed5000PortC3Discards.description: This object counts the number of Class 3 frames that the port has discarded.

ed5000PortMcastTimedOuts.name: ed5000PortMcastTimedOuts
ed5000PortMcastTimedOuts.description: This object counts the number of Multicast frames that has been timed out.

ed5000PortTxMcasts.name: ed5000PortTxMcasts
ed5000PortTxMcasts.description: This object counts the number of Multicast frames that has been transmitted.

ed5000PortTxThroughput.name: ed5000PortTxThroughput
ed5000PortTxThroughput.description: This object presents the Bps transmission rate.

ed5000PortRxThroughput.name: ed5000PortRxThroughput
ed5000PortRxThroughput.description: This object presents the Bps reception rate.

ed5000PortScn.name: ed5000PortScn
ed5000PortScn.description: An ed5000PortScn(1) is generated whenever a Fc_Port changes its operational state. For instance, the Fc_Port goes from on-line to offline.

ed5000FruScn.name: ed5000FruScn
ed5000FruScn.description: An ed5000FruScn(2) is generated whenever a FRU status changes its operational state.
